      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>CAFE DE BRUXELLES</p>
        <p>Solid bistro cooking and a good selection of beer are the specialty at this charming Belgian restaurant. Appetizers on the current menu include leek gratin; snails served in a Roquefort cream; gratineed baked mussels, and salade Liegoise combining endive, sauteed potatoes, string beans, and bacon in a sherry vinaigrette. French fries can also be served as an appetizer. For the main course, there is roast monkfish with mustard sauce and braised endives; grilled pork chops with a compote of apples, onions and prunes; seared sweetbreads with salsifis and wild mushrooms, and grilled salmon with a shrimp-scented bearnaise. (Diner's Journal: 2/4/94)  GOOD EATING</p>
      </block>
